<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-15T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-15T08:00:00-05:00" n="240" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d240">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/8770: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-15T22:00:00+09:00">July 15, 1937—10
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 15—10:15 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>202. My 201, July 15, 9 p.m. It has just been announced that the Cabinet
                            has decided to despatch to North China reenforcements of undisclosed
                            number of troops.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Peiping.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>